The National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa and Solidarity have signed a wage agreement with the Steel and Engineering Industries Federation of South Africa. CAPE TOWN - A strike threatening to bring the engineering sector to halt has been averted.The National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) and Solidarity have signed a wage agreement with the Steel and Engineering Industries Federation of South Africa.Numsa says it will announce the details of the agreement on Wednesday.But it had previously requested a 15% increase across the board.